PrecisAuthority for the Minister of Foreign Affairs (a) to sign, subject to ratification, the WORLD INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY ORGANIZATION (WIPO) PERFORMANCES AND PHONOGRAMS TREATY (GENEVA, 1996), or (b) to issue an Instrument of Full Powers authorizing the Honourable Sheila Copps, or the Honourable John Manley, or John Weekes, Ambassador to the Permanent Mission of Canada to the World Trade Organization, to sign, subject to ratification, the said Treaty, on behalf of the Government of Canada.
